https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/git/trees{/sha}","updated_at":"2026-05-01T11:39:55Z","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind","visibility":"public","watchers":61,"watchers_count":61,"web_commit_signoff_required":false},"sha":"4ca891556708448f0d549fd1cc357fd779736428","user":{"avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/245352401?v=4","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/events{/privacy}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/gists{/gist_id}","gravatar_id":"","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant","id":245352401,"login":"link-assistant","node_id":"O_kgDODp_H0Q","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/repos","site_admin":false,"starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/subscriptions","type":"Organization","url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant","user_view_type":"public"}},"body":"## Summary\n\nExpands the experimental hidden `--use-agent-commander` path so hive-mind can execute every currently supported tool through `agent-commander@^0.6.0`: `claude`, `codex`, `opencode`, `agent`, `qwen`, and `gemini`.\n\nDefault behavior stays unchanged when the flag is absent: existing embedded adapters continue to handle direct tool execution. Gemini is exposed through the opt-in agent-commander path, and the Telegram `/gemini` alias adds `--tool gemini --use-agent-commander` automatically.\n\n## What Changed\n\n- Upgraded `agent-commander` to `^0.6.0` and validated all six tools against its exported support list.\n- Extended the agent-commander adapter with model alias normalization, Claude/Codex option parity where upstream supports passthrough, Qwen/Gemini prompt support, Playwright MCP hint checks, and metadata-based result normalization.\n- Added Gemini model aliases/defaults and display/model-info coverage alongside existing Claude, Codex, OpenCode, Agent, and Qwen model handling.\n- Updated solve/restart validation so `--use-agent-commander` owns the agent-commander execution path while direct execution remains the default path.\n- Added Telegram `/gemini` alias support, Gemini queue tracking, documentation updates, changeset text, and the issue 1043 case-study evidence.\n\n## Upstream Follow-Up\n\n`agent-commander@0.6.0` now supports all six tool names, but Qwen and Gemini still lack some parity surfaces available to Claude/Codex/OpenCode/Agent, especially prompt-file handling and executable/env/extra-arg passthrough. Reported upstream:\n\n- https://github.com/link-assistant/agent-commander/issues/35\n\nEarlier parity issues are now closed:\n\n- https://github.com/link-assistant/agent-commander/issues/29\n- https://github.com/link-assistant/agent-commander/issues/30\n\n## Verification\n\nPost-merge with current `origin/main` (`1.62.1`):\n\n- `node tests/test-agent-commander-option.mjs`\n- `node tests/test-issue-882-fixes.mjs`\n- `node tests/model-info.test.mjs`\n- `node tests/test-telegram-bot-command-aliases.mjs`\n- `node tests/solve-queue-tool-tracking.test.mjs`\n- `node tests/solve-queue.test.mjs`\n- `node tests/test-qwen-support.mjs`\n- `npm run format:check`\n- `npm run lint`\n- `npm test` (all 81 selected test files passed)\n\nNo UI changes, so screenshots are not applicable.\n\nResolves #1043\n","changed_files":52,"closed_at":null,"comments":11,"comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1044/comments","commits":9,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/1044/commits","created_at":"2025-12-31T12:11:13Z","deletions":96,"diff_ur